SIMPLE: plentiful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plentiful
<hw>Plen"ti*ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Containing plenty; copious; abundant; ample; <as>as, a
<ex>plentiful</ex> harvest; a <ex>plentiful</ex> supply of
water.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Yielding abundance; prolific; fruitful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If it be a long winter, it is commonly a more <qex>plentiful</qex>
year.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Lavish; profuse; prodigal.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He that is <qex>plentiful</qex> in expenses will hardly be
preserved from</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Plen"ti*ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Plen"ti*ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plenty</ent>⟦br⟧
